-- Hamels Agrees to $144 Million Deal With Phillies, USA Today Says
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2012-07-25T12:31:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-25/hamels-agrees-to-144-million-deal-with-phillies-usa-today-says.html
The Philadelphia Phillies agreed to
a six-year contract worth $144 million with starting pitcher
 Cole Hamels , USA Today reported, citing a person with direct
knowledge of the negotiations.  The team has scheduled an afternoon news conference, the
newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  